text: Benjamin hielke de Roo (11 February 1940 - 17 May 2016) was an Dutch-born Australian gymnast. He was born in Enschede, the Netherlands. In 1957 his family immigrated to Australia. In 1960, he became Australian citizen. He competed for Australia at the 1960 and 1964 Summer Olympics. De Roo died at a hospital in Katoomba, New South Wales on 17 May 2016 from complications of a stroke, aged 76. ==References== Category:1940 births Category:2016 deaths Category:Competitors at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:1964 Summer Olympics Category:Olympians for Australia Category:Deaths from stroke Category:Gymnasts Category:Naturalised citizens of Australia Category:People from Enschede Category:Sportspeople from Overijssel
